      "id": "2c1a0013-0000-0000-0000-000000000013",
      "name": "Audit log",
      "type": "n8n-nodes-base.noOp",
      "typeVersion": 1,
      "position": [2680, 360]
    },
    {
      "parameters": {
        "content": "## W2 — Morning Risk Sweep\n\nScheduled, read-only daily scan of today's orders.\nScores each order, ranks risk, and posts one digest to Slack.\n\n**Zero backend change** — uses only endpoints that already exist:\nGET /orders/today and POST /orders/{id}/evaluate.\n\nFlow: Trigger → Fetch → Decide → Score (throttled) → Rank → Digest → Notify → Audit.",
        "height": 260,
        "width": 360,
        "color": 4
      },
      "id": "2c1a00a1-0000-0000-0000-0000000000a1",
      "name": "Note: Overview",
      "type": "n8n-nodes-base.stickyNote",
      "typeVersion": 1,
      "position": [200, 40]
    },
    {
      "parameters": {
        "content": "### Score & Throttle\n\nFan-out: one evaluate call per order.\nHTTP **batching** (5 items / 1000 ms) protects the model service from saturation.\n`onError: continueRegularOutput` + 3 retries: one bad order never aborts the sweep — it is flagged `scored_ok=false` and counted in the digest.",
        "height": 240,
        "width": 420,
        "color": 5
      },
      "id": "2c1a00a2-0000-0000-0000-0000000000a2",
      "name": "Note: Scoring",
      "type": "n8n-nodes-base.stickyNote",
      "typeVersion": 1,
      "position": [1100, -20]
    },
    {
      "parameters": {
        "content": "### Digest, Notify & Audit\n\nAggregate → single summary item, so a **zero-high-risk** morning still sends an 'all clear' and still writes an audit record.\n\nAudit = the `audit` object on the final item, persisted by n8n's execution log (see workflow Settings → Save successful executions).",
        "height": 260,
        "width": 420,
        "color": 6
      },
      "id": "2c1a00a3-0000-0000-0000-0000000000a3",
      "name": "Note: Digest",
      "type": "n8n-nodes-base.stickyNote",
      "typeVersion": 1,
      "position": [2200, 40]
    }
  ],
